    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Deserved Peace Prize</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Edward W Poitras letter lauds granting of Nobel Peace Prize to South Korea Pres Kim Dae Jung</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''South Korea's Peacemaker'' (editorial, Oct. 15):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''South Korea's Peacemaker'' (editorial, Oct. 15):</p>
        <p>There are two dimensions likely to be overlooked in the expressions of satisfaction at the well-deserved granting of a Nobel Peace Prize to President Kim Dae Jung of South Korea.</p>
        <p>First, Mr. Kim has been the first East Asian leader to make clear that the pursuit of basic human rights is not a surrender to imported Western values but an authentic Asian affirmation of universal principles.</p>
        <p>Second, the indispensable role of his wife, Dr. Lee Hee Ho, should be remembered as President Kim is honored. She took to the streets, maintained communication and struggled endlessly to generate  the support that eventually led to  the sparing of her husband's life and his eventual release and return to political leadership.</p>
        <p>EDWARD W. POITRAS  Freeport, Me., Oct. 16, 2000</p>
      </block>
